5:
There's no end to them! Alk, we
should retreat for the time being!
10:
We might have to do that... There's
just too many!
19:
Wah-haha! Monsters, you face the
soon-to-be-famous adventurer
GRIEG. Remember my name!
27:
Hey, thank you so much for helping
us out back there!
31:
Nah, don't sweat it, man! No biggie. I
eat scrubs like those for lunch—
35:
Or was it breakfast? Brunch? Dinner?
Or is it supper? You know I never
could get those two straight—
39:
I think most people just say
"breakfast".
44:
Right! Yeah, exactly! Thanks man,
you've got a good set of shoulders
on your head!
48:
H-huh? Anyway, your assistance
was much appreciated. Be careful
around these parts, though.
Monsters are out in unprecedented
numbers.
52:
Oh, believe me, I know! Those guys
are persistent as hell! Before I knew
it, I was up to my knees in them...
57:
Wait, does that mean they're here
'cause they followed YOU?
62:
They're pouring in from this side; it's
no longer safe! We must retreat!
65: Leave the rear guard to ME!
70:
It's no use. We're surrounded by
monsters on all sides...
77:
I suppose all that's left to do is...
charge right on through them!
82:
Are you crazy? We'd never make it
out alive! Also, isn't that exactly how
you got us into this mess in the first
place?!
85:
Hahaha! Wow, now that you
mention it, that IS what happened...
90:
Try thinking this through carefully for
once! Okay?!
94:
Right, thinking, yeah. I can do that.
That's when the brain goes BRRR,
right? I'm familiar with that.
98:
Hmm... But then if...
Carry the two... Cross the Ts...
Gahhhhhh...
102:
Er, okay, I'm sorry, if it's too much for
you, just forget—
115:
Yes! I.... am going to SMASH THIS
WITH MY AXE. That will open a hole
so we can escape! It's a flawless
plan.
118: Wait a minute, is that really—
121:
Yaaaaah! Don't worry. Just LEAVE IT
TO ME!
133:
S-sorry... I just really thought that
would be a good idea...
137:
Don't apologize—your little plan
might just have saved us!
141:
The monsters are all scattered and
confused... This might be our chance
to break through!
144:
Hahaha! That was all totally
according to plan!
157:
Leave this one to ME! The two of you
get out of here, pronto!
161:
...I'm sorry, grandpa. I don't have
what it takes to be the greatest
adventurer in the world after all...
167:
That doesn't mean you can just give
up! We're not letting you die here on
your own!
175:
We fight together, Grieg. You're one
of us—there's no way we're leaving
here without you.
179:
We've got a clear path ahead! All we
need to do is retreat slowly while
dispatching the rest. We can do this!
191:
Phew... I was sure we were goners
that time!
195:
That was amazing! We were about
to die... but then we didn't! You guys
are incredible!
199:
We only made it out because of you,
Grieg! You held off those monsters
like a champ. Seriously, you're built
like a tank!
202:
Indeed, your strength is
commendable. If it weren't for you,
we might have perished. You have
my thanks, Grieg!
206:
Th-that... is the first time anyone's
said that to me...
211:
Listen, Grieg. I was thinking... Why
don't you join our party permanently?
214:
Exploring the Kaleidoscope on your
own is really inefficient. You can
team up with us whenever it's
convenient for you!
221:
I understand! I see! That is an
EXCELLENT idea! Starting today, I'm
one of you guys!
224: You can leave EVERYTHING to me!
228: Well, I don't know about EVERYTHING.
